						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up to the east of the Gangamma shrine.</p>						

						<p>This is an undated epigraph and may be assigned to the 15th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a temple in Anantapuram situated in the Mallikārjuni<hi rend="italic">sīma</hi> and the consecration in it of the goddess Gaṅgadēvi by Gaṅgana, son of Abbana and Gaṅgasāni.</p>						

						</summary>
